@translation labeled en project



@(1) Say to my king, @lab{2}thus says Aradmu, your servant:


@(3)(Concerning the matter of ) Abaindasa, captain of the royal army,
that my king sent me (a message) about; @lab{4}my king must be informed
about the matter.


@(5)When I focused my attention on Zimudar, @lab{6}I was in the process
of mustering troops for my king’s expedition, @lab{7}but when Abaindasa
inspected those troops, @lab{8}2000 of those men were missing. @lab{9}He had not
gone to ..., nor had he returned. @lab{10}He had abandoned the fortress, o
my king, and then (re)captured (it)! @lab{11}That crime was a very serious crime
against my king! @lab{12–13} ...


@(14)Whatever you, my king order me to do, (I will do)! @lab{15}This my king
should know!


