#lem: ŋaʾe[I]IP; zig[rise]; n; gaz[to kill, slaughter]V/t; n; dab[to seize, take, hold]V/t

7.	ka-ku-la-tum{ki}-šè ba-ni-kur₉
#lem: Kakkulatum[1]SN; kur[to enter, to be brought in]V/i

8.	tukum-bi lugal-ŋu₁₀ ugnim-ma tuš-ù-bi ab-bé
#lem: tukum[if]CNJ; lugal[king]N; ugnim[army, troops]N; tuš[to sit (down)]V/i; e[speak]

9.	{kuš}a-ŋá-lá keše₂-da-bi šu hé-mi-ib-da₁₃-da₁₃
#lem:  aŋala[leather sack]; kešed[to bind]V/t; šu[hand]N; taka[set aside]

10.	tukum-bi lugal-ŋu₁₀ ugnim-ma nu-tuš-ù-bi ab-bé
#lem: tukum[if]CNJ; lugal[king]N; ugnim[army, troops]N; tuš[to sit (down)]V/i; e[to speak]V/t

11.	hé-em-ma-su₈-ge-eš
#lem: sug[stand]

12.	lugal-ŋu₁₀ hé-en-zu
#lem: lugal[king]N; zu[to know, learn]V/t


@translation labeled en project



@(1)Say to my king, @lab{2–3}thus says Sîn-tillati, the frontier commander, your
servant:


@(4)When I went upstream to Kakkulatum, @lab{5}the armed Amurrum
ambushed (us). @lab{6}When I (counter) attacked, I slaughtered 600 (of
them), captured 1200 (and) @lab{7}brought (the captives) into Kakkulatum.


@(8)If my king commands (the captives) to camp among the army, @lab{9}let
him send provisions for them. @lab{10}If my king does not order them to
camp among the army, @lab{11}he should put them into service (elsewhere).

@(12)This my king should know.

