@translation labeled en project


@(2)Say @lab{1}to Sîn-tillati, the frontier commander, @lab{3}thus says Iddin-Dagan,
your king:


@(4)Thanks to you, my expeditionary force can (now) cross from one
bank of the river to another. inspiring fear and causing a blockade.


@(5)When you went upstream to Kakkulatum, @lab{6}(the gods) Lamma, Dagan,
Kabta (and) Enlil caused the (enemy) troops to submit.^1^ @lab{7}My splendor
covers the homeland, @lab{8}while you approached the enemy land with
your heroism and your strength.^2^ @lab{9}You have been able to make prisoners of the enemy.


@(10)After (that) man’s troops have left the city, @lab{11}once you have inspected
the army, @lab{12–13}then let go of the lowest (ranking) in order to safeguard
their (other) prisoners.^3^ @lab{14}Let those who enter and leave (the city)
work!

@(15)Their famous kings and armed forces were brought in your path,

@(17)do not diminish your army!^4^ @lab{18}Come quickly! @lab{19}It is urgent!

# #note: ^1^ Var (X8): Lamma, Dagan and Kabta took possession of all these troops.
# #note: ^2^ Var (X8): and you, who knows my strength and heroism, approached the enemy land.
# #note: ^3^ Var ll. 11–13 (N88, X3): Release the lowest (ranking) of their army that you took hold of. (*Note X3 omits line 12).
# #note: ^4^ Var (Ur11, X8): Approach their army, do not tarry!


