@translation labeled en project



@(2)Say @lab{1}to my king, the sparkling-eyed bull who wears a lapis beard^1^:
Repeat to @lab{3}the golden statue, born on a favorable day,^2^ @lab{4}zebu
reared in the divine sheepfold, chosen by the shining heart of Inana,

@(5)my lord, the trusted of Inana:


@(6)By your form, you are the child of An. @lab{7}Your command, like the
words of a god, is irrevocable.^3^ @lab{8}Your words, like raindrops that fall
from the sky, are uncountable.


@(9)Thus says Ur-saga, your servant:


@(10)My king has not investigated my case (but) I am a citizen of Ur!^4^

@(11)If it is satisfying to my king, @lab{12}then let no one make off with my
father’s estate. @lab{13}Let no one forcibly take away the foundation of my
father’s estate. @lab{14}This my lord should know!

^1^Uk2 gloss: Say to my king who is like a sparkling-eyed bull.
^2^Uk2 gloss: statue of gold, born on a favorable day.
^3^Var (Ur4): You command is the word of a god, all the lands cannot reverse it.
^4^Var (N87, Ur4, Uk1, U2): Has my king investigated my case? I am a citizen of Ur!

