@translation labeled en project

@(1)Nippurtalu, @lab{2}son of Lugal-šuba, the merchant, @lab{4}fashioned a heavenly axe @lab{3}for Nergal.

@(5)Its wood of the arganum-tree of the mountain @lab{6}is superior to the
alal(-stone). @lab{7}Its stone is antasura, @lab{8}which has no rival.

@(9)When he strikes (with it), may his arm never tire. @lab{10}Should it break,

@(11)I will repair it for him. @lab{12}Should he lose it, @lab{13}I will replace it for him.

@(14)As long as I lie may I be regarded (with benevolence). @lab{15}When I die

@(16)may I drink clear water in the netherworld.


