@translation labeled en project

@(1)Say to our king, @lab{2}thus says the governor (and) chief temple administrator:

@(3)The Dabta ﬁeld—3000 ha @lab{10,800 iku}—(4)(is the) ešgar (ﬁeld)
of Enlil, Ninlil and Ninurta. @lab{5}From it: 150 ha @lab{540 iku} are
the sustenance ﬁelds of the men in charge of the
requisitions. @lab{6}50 ha @lab{180 iku} is (the area at) the lower
end of the ﬁeld. @lab{7}(About this) Iqbišum and Abi-qati instituted a
claim.

@(8)If our king consents, @lab{9}he should send a courier and @lab{10}[give] (us) an
order (regarding) the work and the boundary of the ﬁeld.

@(11)0.5 ha (2 iku) at its back and 50[+x] ha (180[+x] iku) at
the edge of the ﬁeld @lab{12}were broken up with hoes (and so)
prepared. @lab{13}There being no replacement workers, farmers,
ox-drivers or plowmen, @lab{14}the ﬁeld was harrowed (only) with
individual oxen. @lab{15}We are (only) working with hoes! This our
king should know.


