#note: ^1^ Variant (X4): [l]ú-tur silim-ma-ni ad-da-[a?-ni?] KA-za in-tuku.


@translation labeled en project

@(1)Say to Lugal-ibila, @lab{2}thus says Inim-Inana:

@(3)Do not neglect Sumerian! @lab{4}For the second time, I am sending you a
message in the proper language.

@(5 - 6)Do not let the children seated before you leave school. @lab{7}Moreover,
should someone try to deceive you @lab{8}saying to you “I want to go” on
the authority of his father, @lab{9}until you and I have discussed the proper
time @lab{10}(and/or) I send someone to you (with the OK), @lab{11}do not let any
of the kids go! @lab{12}You are responsible for ...^1^ It is urgent!

# #note: ^1^ Variant (X4): “his father has entrusted the welfare of the child
# to you (lit: in your mouth).” I have restored this line following that
# preserved in the late period redaction of this letter, the letter of
# Lugal-ibila to Lugal-nesage line 21, for which see Civil 2000a, 109ff.


