#lem: diŋir[deity, god, goddess]N; lu[person]N; kur[a unit of capacity]N; did[lawsuit, trial]N; me[to be]V/i; šag[heart]N; ki[place]N; gi[to change status]V/i

#note: ^1^ Var (Su2): diŋir-ŋu10 lú kúr-zu nu-me-en ba-ar-mé en-tar-re.


@translation labeled en project

@(1)Say to my god, @lab{2}thus says Gudea, your servant:

@(3)Like a sheep, who has no reliable shepherd, @lab{4}I have no reliable
herdsman to guide me. @lab{5}(Instead) I have been forced to accompany an
imprudent merchant. @lab{6}Like a donkey he [strikes? me] (with) a brutal
whip.  @lab{7}I am important, but I must say nothing; has he seen that I
am vigilant? @lab{8}Seven times my doing this has not ... @lab{9}At it’s side,
seven times, I have not found/recognized him. @lab{10}My god, I am not one
who speaks angrily! May your heart revert to its previous sentiment
for me!^1^

# #note: ^1^Var (Su2): My god, I am not your enemy. Inquire about me!


