@translation labeled en project

@(1)Say to Nudimmudsiga, @lab{2}thus says Igmil-Sin, your father:

@(3 - 4)When I arrived as governor @lab{3}to Dunnum, on the bank of the
Amar-Suen canal, @lab{5}(all) the students, from the youngest to the
eldest, @lab{6}from the ones doing the series @meme, to the ones doing an
array of (compositions on) tablets, @lab{7}from the ones doing
multiplication tablets to the ones doing their business accounts,

@(8)the ones doing incantations, the ones who interpret songs,

@(10)during the day and into the night I had them write @lab{9}their
multi-column tablets, their single-column tablets (or) their
lenticular tablets. @lab{11}I had them deposited in my “hand” basket(s).


@(12)For your part, you transferred the (texts of the balaŋ) @uru
@am-ma-irra-bi. @lab{13}The ones (who write) their single-column
tablets ... @lab{14}the ones (who write) accounts ...

$ (ca. 10 lines missing)

$ 2 lines unclear

@(17)Your gift [...]. @lab{18}My well-being, [your] well-being, @lab{19}and the well
being of the students [...]. @lab{20}Liburam [...]. @lab{21}Like my changed city,
my heart will [...].


