#lem: did[lawsuit, trial]N; heše[oppressed]; e[speak]

8.	mu di-da-ka-ni igi-zu-šè KA bal-e
#lem: mu[year]N; did[lawsuit, trial]N; igi[eye]N; KA[unmng]N; bala[to turn, rotate, turn over]V/t

9.	lú mu-e-ši-in-gi₄ gú-zu na-an-šub-bé-en
#lem: lu[person]N; gi[to turn, return]V/i; gu[neck]N; šub[to fall]V/i

10.	a-ma-ru-kam
#lem: amaru[flood]N


@translation labeled en project



@(1)Say to Nur-Kabta, @lab{2}thus says Sa@-lugalbi-zu:


@(3)When you (together with) the zabardab and the chief singer, @lab{4}detained
Ku-Ninlila at the Abulmah gate, @lab{5}Ur-Sin procured ... -lugalŋu (to act)
as baliff in order to (obtain) the return of the ﬁeld.


@(6)If in your true heart you are my brother, @lab{7}do not mistreat me because
of my case! @lab{8}Because (he wishes) to discuss his case with you, @lab{9}I am
sending you a man. You must not neglect him! @lab{10}It is urgent!

